# Java HackerRank Solutions

Welcome to the **Java HackerRank** repository! 👨‍💻📘  
This project contains a collection of Java solutions for various coding challenges and algorithm problems found on [HackerRank](https://www.hackerrank.com/). These problems range from beginner to intermediate levels and cover topics like data structures, object-oriented programming, loops, arrays, and more.

---

## 📁 Repository Structure

Each folder or Java file represents a standalone solution to a HackerRank problem, with clear and concise code using best practices.


---

## ✅ What You’ll Find

- 🧠 **Algorithmic Thinking**: Clean, well-commented solutions to enhance your problem-solving skills.
- 💻 **Object-Oriented Design**: Use of classes, methods, and encapsulation.
- 🔁 **Control Structures**: Loops, conditionals, and switch-case usage.
- 🧪 **Practice Exercises**: Ideal for those preparing for coding interviews or brushing up on Java fundamentals.

---

## 🚀 How to Use

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/hoyjaren/Java-HackerRank.git

2. Open the project in your favorite Java IDE (e.g., IntelliJ IDEA or Eclipse).

3. Navigate to the src/ directory and run the desired Java file.

 Requirements
- Java JDK 8 or above
- Any Java-compatible IDE or terminal setup

Topics Covered
✅ Basic I/O

✅ Strings

✅ Loops & Conditionals

✅ Classes & Objects

✅ Inheritance & Interfaces

✅ ArrayLists & Arrays

✅ Exception Handling

